@startuml seq_03_forgot_password
title Sequence Diagram: UC-03 Forgot Password

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Auth Controller" as Controller
participant "Auth Service" as Service
participant "User Repository" as Repo
participant "Redis Cache" as Redis
participant "Email Service" as Email

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open the Forgot Password page
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Enter email
User -> Frontend: (3.1) Submit email
Frontend -> Controller: (3.2) POST /api/auth/forgot-password {email}
Controller -> Service: (4.1) Validate email
Service -> Repo: (5.1) Look up account
Repo --> Service: (5.2) User found (local auth)
Service -> Redis: (6.1) Create OTP and reset request
Service -> Email: (9.1) Send reset OTP email
Email --> Service: (9.2) Email sent
Service --> Controller: (9.3) Success
Controller --> Frontend: (9.4) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (9.5) Prompt for OTP

User -> Frontend: (10.1) Enter received OTP
User -> Frontend: (11.1) Submit OTP
Frontend -> Controller: (11.2) POST /api/auth/verify-reset-otp {email, otp}
Controller -> Service: (12.1) Verify OTP
Service -> Redis: (12.2) Check OTP
Redis --> Service: (12.3) OTP matches
Service -> Redis: (13.1) Generate reset token
Service --> Controller: (13.2) Success (reset token)
Controller --> Frontend: (13.3) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (13.4) Prompt for new password

User -> Frontend: (15.1) Enter new password and confirm password
User -> Frontend: (16.1) Submit password reset
Frontend -> Controller: (16.2) POST /api/auth/reset-password {email, token, new_password}
Controller -> Service: (17.1) Validate new password
Service -> Redis: (17.2) Validate reset token
Redis --> Service: (17.3) Token valid
Service -> Service: (18.1) Hash new password (bcrypt)
Service -> Repo: (18.2) Update user password
Repo --> Service: (18.3) Password updated
Service -> Redis: (19.1) Delete reset request
Service --> Controller: (19.2) Success
Controller --> Frontend: (19.3) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (19.4) Redirect to login page
@enduml
